&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;There has never been a better time to join us in our Emergency Department as we continue to invest and develop our staff. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are passionate about providing outstanding care to our patients and believe that investing in our staff is a key part of achieving this. Our elite Emergency Department team will support and guide you to build a career that you will be proud off.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be part of a team that can deal with anything and everything, so if you are full of enthusiasm, commitment and professionalism we would love to hear from you. The Emergency Department (Basingstoke) is part of Hampshire Hospitals Foundation Trust. We are a dedicated team of professionals who aspire to provide high standards of care for all our patients, both adults and children. Our dedicated children’s area opened recently and provides a safe place for children to be seen and treated whilst under our care. Our newly opened Rapid Assessment and Treatment area and Emergency Decision Unit are also part of our newly renovated and expanding department.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;All our staff receive a comprehensive induction and initial supernumerary period, a programme of education and development within the department, as well as regular performance reviews.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We value all backgrounds. This role is open to newly qualified nurses supported by a great preceptorship programme.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Flexible working patterns will considered for all nursing applicants!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For more information:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Read our Trainee ACPs&#39; story about working in ED Basingstoke and watch our video in the links to find out more about working with us. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We welcome questions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Laura Good - Sister - ED Basingstoke&lt;/p&gt;
